{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Japan Trip 2015 Part 3: Nara","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\tWe arrived in Nara on the afternoon of the 23rd after spending the morning in Kyoto. On the cab ride to our AirBnB we were caught off-guard by the amount of deer. They were seriously friggin&#x2019; everywhere! They walked around casually on major streets like they ran the place.</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<h3>Nara Park</h3>\n<p>After dropping our stuff off at the AirBnB, we headed for Nara Park where we were greeted by more deer. They were all really chill and friendly; you could go up close to them and they wouldn&#x2019;t care. We bought some deer cookies to feed them, though it was a bit scary because they come at you in droves. You never know if they&#x2019;ll suddenly head-butt your candy ass.</p>\n<p style=\"width: 100%; height: 0px; position: relative; padding-bottom: 56.250%;\"><iframe src=\"https://streamable.com/e/wdvi?logo=0\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen webkitallowfullscreen mozallowfullscreen scrolling=\"no\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; position: absolute;\"></iframe></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Feeding dem deers &#x2013; sorry for the vertical video. Music by <a href=\"http://turdmussel.com/\">TURD MUSSEL</a></div>\n<h3>Todaiji</h3>\n<p>After we got tired of the deer we walked over to Todaiji Temple, home of the giant, 15-metre Buddha statue. I was in awe at the size of the temple. Hands down the biggest temple I&#x2019;ve ever seen in my life!</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:1024px\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:66.66666666666667%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/bb385/DSCF0779.jpg 256w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/ab422/DSCF0779.jpg 512w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/1f853/DSCF0779.jpg 1024w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/05429/DSCF0779.jpg 1224w\" src=\"/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/1f853/DSCF0779.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" srcset=\"/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/bb385/DSCF0779.jpg 256w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/ab422/DSCF0779.jpg 512w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/1f853/DSCF0779.jpg 1024w,\n/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/05429/DSCF0779.jpg 1224w\" src=\"/static/7bd638f6ebc256fa9e808437ccd63f9d/1f853/DSCF0779.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<p>The sheer size of the buddha statue gave me the chills&#x2026; mostly because it reminded me of an episode in the manga <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gantz\">GANTZ</a> when they fight the <a href=\"http://i.imgur.com/K1E4sZM.png\">giant buddha statue</a>. I looked into his friendly face and wondered, &#x201C;what if he suddenly stood up and started stomping everyone? Is there a good hiding place nearby? Which friend would I be okay with leaving behind?&#x201D;. These are important questions to ask when looking at big statues.</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%;width:683px\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:150%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px\" srcset=\"/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/62e39/DSCF0766.jpg 171w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/bd96c/DSCF0766.jpg 342w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/6298b/DSCF0766.jpg 683w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/692ab/DSCF0766.jpg 816w\" src=\"/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/6298b/DSCF0766.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 683px) 100vw, 683px\" srcset=\"/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/62e39/DSCF0766.jpg 171w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/bd96c/DSCF0766.jpg 342w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/6298b/DSCF0766.jpg 683w,\n/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/692ab/DSCF0766.jpg 816w\" src=\"/static/56f872ca2c33875058e02030ee485a7c/6298b/DSCF0766.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">15-metre tall Buddha</div>\n<h3>Back to the AirBnB</h3>\n<p>Our AirBnB was really cool. It was a very traditional house in rural Nara that we had all to ourselves. This was a nice change as our previous AirBnB was pretty cramped.</p>\n<p></p><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:56.38461538461539%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/aca85/DSCF1708.jpg 163w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/0954f/DSCF1708.jpg 325w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/a111b/DSCF1708.jpg 650w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/ce471/DSCF1708.jpg 975w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/bee4e/DSCF1708.jpg 1300w\" src=\"/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/a111b/DSCF1708.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/aca85/DSCF1708.jpg 163w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/0954f/DSCF1708.jpg 325w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/a111b/DSCF1708.jpg 650w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/ce471/DSCF1708.jpg 975w,\n/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/bee4e/DSCF1708.jpg 1300w\" src=\"/static/602b18c18c5844ac19f9bc27ca2a9c75/a111b/DSCF1708.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div><p></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">View from the AirBnB. Nothing but fields, deers and wild boars.</div>\n<p>There weren&#x2019;t any bars or shops nearby so we stocked up on beer and spent the night at the AirBnB. We drank lots and played Street Fighter II on Super Famicom all night.</p>\n<p>The next morning we crushed the leftover brews and took the Shinkansen to Hiroshima.</p>\n<h3>Takeaways:</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Nara is nice, but in hindsight we probably didn&#x2019;t have to spend a night there. Nara is really close to both Osaka and Kyoto so if you&#x2019;re staying in either of those cities I&#x2019;d recommend just doing a day trip. </li>\n</ul>\n<hr>\n<p><a href=\"/japan-trip-2015/\">&#x2190; Back to Japan Trip 2015 index</a>\t\t</p>\n</body></html>","wordpress_id":4267},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[{"node":{"content":"<p>@Grant haha, thanks for reading buddy 🙂</p>\n","author_name":"tetchi","date":"November 22nd, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Hahaha</p>\n<p>“what if he suddenly stood up and started stomping everyone? Is there a good hiding place nearby? Which friend would I be okay with leaving behind?”</p>\n","author_name":"Grant Lucas","date":"November 21st, 2015"}}]}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"japan-trip-2015-part-3-nara","wordpressId":4267,"newerPostSlug":"japan-trip-2015-part-4-hiroshima","olderPostSlug":"japan-trip-2015-part-2-kyoto"}}